We need to create query class first before we create a Security policy 
To create the Query 
>> Select AddNewItem >> DataModel >> Query >> Give the name to it.
>> Drag the table which we are creating on to the DataSource
>> Properties :- set the Dynamic Fields property to >> NO 
                 Add the Filed to the Fields List and Drag the same feild on to the RangesNode.
                 change the value property of the rangenode to According.
>> Save and close

To Create the Security policy 
>> Add the NewItem and select the security and Security Policy from the left hand side.
>>Properties :- set label to it.
                give the table name as the primary table property
                query property give it the Policy Name
                UseNotExistJoin to NO
                Constraines Table to Yes 
                Operation as Select 
Create a security role and in the property of Security Policy 
               set context type to RoleName
               set the Role Name
               Set the Enabled Property to Yes.

